Let’s show some love to the chefs & culinary folks that put Charlotte on the map! We’re thrilled to announce the launch of our Kings & Queens dinner series. Sounds by @justbmannodj, beer from @freerangebrew and cocktails by @thirdeyekitty!

Brunch will begin with a champagne cocktail, followed by bread service, cold appetizer, hot appetizer, fish, meat and dessert.

Click through the link in bio to get tickets via @opentable (select April 9, noon "experiences").
A few things to know before you go:

When purchasing tickets please make note of your food allergies.

We will not be able to accommodate guests who are vegetarian/vegan.

All tickets sold are NON-REFUNDABLE.
In that case that you must cancel, you will be cancelled WITHOUT refund.

You may give your prepaid tickets to another guest that may fill your space.

📣UPDATE: SOLD OUT!! Queen City, we have an early holiday gift for you! Leah & Louise will host @tonitiptonmartin : one of the most authoritative voices on Black and African American Foodways. We will explore the history of black beverage culture, history, and its traditions through archival recipes and modern interpretations directly from her latest book, "Juke Joints, Jazz Clubs & Juice". 

This dinner will feature five courses prepared by Chef Gregory Collier at our very own juke joint. Dinner will be paired with cocktails inspired by the book and a mocktail pairing option will be available as well. Books are available for pre-order when booking dinner tickets. 

Join us for a night of literature, libations, and history with Toni Tipton- Martin on Tuesday, December 12th, 2023, at 6:30pm. There will be one seating only. Please email gm@leahandlouise.com for allergy accommodations.

I met @iamcoopernicus_ a while ago! 2017, I believe! It's been an honor to watch him become the "Jonathan Cooper." 

We had a new menu training, and he kilt these photos, as usual! 

I've been wanting to dabble in cocktail creation, and by no means, am I a mixologist! We have had the amazing talents of two of Charlotte's best mixologists behind our bars, and we've learned a lot.

Every day, @cher.sse and I talk about what is possible how to make it happen. 

These 3 drinks at @leah_and_louise are a result of that curiosity. 

1 Sharing is Caring - @hennessyus cognac, roasted pecan infused Sherry, @grandmarnierusa demerara 

2 Old fashioned - duck fat washed rye, satsuma oleo, orange @angosturahouse bitters, @bittermens orange cream citrate bitters

3 Mezcal Negroni - Goji berry infused mezcal, @lillet.usa rose, @campariamerica

J Coop got us looking like we know how to make some drinks. @cher.sse does, I definitely don't! 🤣🤣🤣
